Dear Parents and Guardians,
Welcome to the 2020-21 school year. HCSS East would like to invite you to our Parent Webinar hosted by Robyn Nelson, HCSS East Director. In this webinar we will cover topics parents need to know to help their child be successful at HCSS East and to start the year off right. Topics include a typical day of remote education, attendance policy, extra curricular activities, and vulnerable students.

You are invited to a Zoom webinar.

Topic: HCSS East Parent Orientation

Register in advance for this webinar:
https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_nY4a5VUcSlaAaMMkc-xBgw

After registering, you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the webinar.

Sincerely,
HCSS Admin

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,
Enclosed is the link to the survey where you will choose which model of learning your child will participate in for the first quarter of the 2020-21 school year.

Survey Link: https://forms.gle/R7pxyTt8krRvGuS4A

We are asking you to complete this survey no later than Friday, August 14th in order for us to plan for the opening. Please complete this survey more than once, if you have multiple children enrolled at HCSS. Please also keep in mind that you will be asked to stick to your choice for at least one marking period.

Yesterday evening HCSS shared our opening plans with you during a webinar on Tuesday, August 11th. If you did not have a chance to watch the webinar, please click https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ee_ioKaCQtM&feature=youtu.be for the video and https://hampdencharter.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/HCSS_Comprehensive-Reopening-Plans-.pdf for the presentation.

Sincerely,
HCSS Administration

Dear Prospective Families,
If your student has been accepted for the 2020-2021 school year at Hampden Charter School of Science-East, you were sent an email with an option to submit required documents via email.

Sincerely,
Hampden Charter School of Science-East

post_text:
Dear HCSS Parents, Students, and Staff,

It’s the Holiday Season!

This is the time of year for people to visit each other, open their homes to visitors, and share
their joy and excitement. It is also the time for us to pause and reflect on our busy lives and be
grateful for many of our blessings. This is one of the greatest times of the year.

I hope you will take this time to relax and spend time with your loved ones. Enjoy your family;
refill your batteries and have this well-deserved break! Safe trips to those of you who take trips
out of town. I ask you, too, to consider those who are less fortunate or in disheartening
circumstances and keep them in your prayers.

I want to take a moment to express my sincere gratitude to all those who help make HCSS a
wonderful place. The new year brings new ways of learning, new challenges, and new fun. I
look forward to what lies ahead of us in 2020 as a school community. In this holiday season and
throughout the New Year, I wish you all love, joy, hope, and happiness.

Sincerely,
Tarkan Topcuoglu
CEO/Superintendent

• Visit www.hampdencharter.org and click “Apply!” under “Admission”

• Call HCSS-East (413) 593-9090 or HCSS-West (413) 278-5450

• Fax the Student Application Form under the “Admission” tab on the
website to HCSS-East (413) 294-2648 or HCSS-West (413) 278 5387

• Attend one of our Open Houses ( See below )

• Deadline: Sunday, March 8, 2020
